definitions.definition: A problem. (clarification of this definition is needed)
A collection of buildings with a common purpose , such as a university or military base.
An assemblage of related things; a collection.

subdefinitions.definition: A cluster of wildfires burning in the same vicinity.
examples: The fire complex began as two separate fires.

subdefinitions.definition: A group of closely related species, often distinguished only with difficulty by traditional morphological methods.

definitions.definition: A group of emotionally charged ideas or mental factors, unconsciously associated by the individual with a particular subject , arising from repressed instincts , fears , or desires and often resulting in mental abnormality .
examples: Jim has a real complex about working for a woman boss.

subdefinitions.definition: A fixed mental tendency or obsession .

definitions.definition: A structure consisting of a central atom or molecule weakly connected to surrounding atoms or molecules, as for example coordination complexes in inorganic chemistry and protein complexes in biochemistry.
A multimorphemic word, one with several parts, one with affixes.
